<head>CAMP</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">營區</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">軍／營</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>PLACE where an ARMY DWELLS.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for a temporary army camp is jūn 軍, and for an army to encamp is to jùn 軍.</p>
<p>2. Yíng 營 refers to a more permanent military camp with defenses.</p>
<p>3. Tún 屯 refers to a defended military settlement of a permanent or semi-permanent kind, a garrison, often on the borders.</p>
        </div>
